cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper discusses a hybrid model of differential privacy for local search, which involves privacy-preserving computation of search logs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with privacy-preserving data management. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the utility of the data, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
